To validate this principle, we further use classic scattering theory to investigate the scattering effects of pores of various sizes in both the visible and MIR bands. The nano-sized pores are designed to be comparable in size to the wavelength of visible light, which is critical for achieving strong reflection in that range. This scattering effect in the visible spectrum can be modeled using Mie scattering theory49, as depicted in Fig. 2k. In the mid-infrared band (7–15 μm), the pore size is significantly smaller than the wavelength, causing Rayleigh scattering to become the dominant scattering mechanism. This can be calculated using the Rayleigh scattering equation49:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
